 L:{em:'☀️',t:'Evaporation',b:'Heat turns water to vapour<br/>Rises up into sky'},R:{em:'☁️',t:'Condensation → Rain',b:'Vapour cools → clouds ☁️<br/>Then falls as 🌧 rain!'},
 fun:'The water you drink today might have been inside a dinosaur! Same water cycles forever! 🦕',tip:'Evaporation = heat added. Condensation = cooling. Precipitation = falls as rain/snow!'},
{q:'What is the difference between conductor and insulator?',a:'Conductors let heat/electricity pass through. Insulators BLOCK it!',
 steps:['CONDUCTOR: heat or electricity flows through EASILY. All metals — copper, iron, aluminium.','INSULATOR: BLOCKS heat or electricity — wood, plastic, rubber, glass, air.','Wires = copper inside (conducts) + plastic outside (insulates). Safe combination!'],
 L:{em:'🥄',t:'Conductor',b:'Metal spoon · Copper wire · Iron nail<br/>Heat + electricity PASS through easily'},R:{em:'🧤',t:'Insulator',b:'Rubber glove · Plastic handle · Wood<br/>Heat + electricity are BLOCKED'},
